params.operator: The operator to add to the allowlist

deregisterOperator(address,address,uint3.details: Reverts for:      - NotAllocationManager: The caller is not the allocation manager

params.operatorSetIds: the list of operator set ids being deregistered from

getAllowedOperators((address,uint32)).details: This function should be used with caution, as it can be expensive to call on-chain

params.operatorSet: The operator set to get the allowed operators from

returns._0: An array of all operators in the allowlist

params.metadataURI: The metadata URI for the AVS

params.operatorSet: The operator set to check the operator in

returns._0: True if the operator is in the allowlist, false otherwise

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

removeOperatorFromAllowlist((address,uin.details: If an operator is removed from the allowlist and is already registered, the avs      must then handle state changes appropriately (ie. eject the operator)Only callable by the owner

params.operator: The operator to remove from the allowlist
params.operatorSet: The operator set to remove the operator from

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby disabling any functionality that is only available to the owner.

returns._0: true if the AVS is supported, false otherwise

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

returns._0: The version string in SemVer format (e.g., "1.1.1")

avs().notice: The AVS that this registrar is for
